04/01/2008
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Chief of General Staff Jovan Lakcevic said Montenegro plans to spend 9.8m euros to modernise the army, a government priority this year.
In remarks Thursday (January 3rd), he noted that 5.1m euros of it would go to the delivery of new armaments and equipment.
In an interview with Vijesti newspaper Friday, Montenegrin Ambassador to NATO Veselin Sukovic said his country is a good example of security and defence sector reforms, stressing NATO shares this view.
Montenegro hopes NATO will invite it to start so-called Intensive Dialogue, the first step towards membership candidate status, during the Alliance summit in April.
(Vijesti - 04/01/08;
RTCG - 03/01/08)
